; Diamond re-enqueue: a row overdeleted in claim round k re-derives
; support for a row that was ALREADY claimed (or eligible to be claimed)
; in an EARLIER round k' < k, stressing the Delta_D discipline
; (plan.md :701-713, "firing over the raw drained queue re-fires an
; already-claimed row on any re-enqueue"). Two independent recursive
; paths converge on the same node so that removing the base fact drains
; through the SCC in multiple rounds and the SAME row (q(4)) is reachable
; via two different chain lengths -- one 1-hop, one 2-hop -- so its
; overdelete claim can be attempted from two different rounds.
#message base(u64 X) @differential.
#message link(u64 From, u64 To) @differential.

#local q(X).

#query q_out(free u64 X).

q(X) : base(X).
q(Y) : q(X), link(X, Y).

q_out(X) : q(X).
